Joseph CLARK, Libelant-Appellee, v. Steam Tug BEAR, Her Engines, etc.; Cornell Steamboat Company, Claimant-Appellant. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 15, 1926.) No. 208. *609Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell, Hiekox & Keating, of New York City (Robert S. Erskine and Henry P. Elliott, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Maeklin, Brown & Van Wyck, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, HAND, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (11 F.[2d] 607) affirmed.
